@host = http://localhost:8080

### health check
GET {{host}}/api/health/ping


### create space
POST {{host}}/api/spaces
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "backend-team",
  "description": "Knowledge space for backend team"
}


### list spaces
GET {{host}}/api/spaces


### get space by id
GET {{host}}/api/spaces/1


### update space
PUT {{host}}/api/spaces/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "backend-team",
  "description": "Updated knowledge space for backend team"
}


### create document
POST {{host}}/api/documents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "spaceId": 1,
  "title": "Spring Boot Service Layer Notes",
  "content": "The service layer is used to organize business logic. Controllers should not directly call database mappers. In this project, the controller receives HTTP requests and delegates business operations to the service layer. The service layer validates business rules, manages transactions, and coordinates database operations. This design makes the project easier to maintain and easier to explain in interviews. When building a RAG application, documents are stored first, then split into chunks, and later converted into embeddings.",
  "sourceType": "MANUAL",
  "sourceUri": "manual-input"
}


### list all documents
GET {{host}}/api/documents


### list documents by space
GET {{host}}/api/documents?spaceId=1


### get document by id
GET {{host}}/api/documents/1


### list document chunks
GET {{host}}/api/documents/1/chunks


### update document
PUT {{host}}/api/documents/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "spaceId": 1,
  "title": "Updated Spring Boot Service Layer Notes",
  "content": "The service layer contains business logic and transaction boundaries. In a clean backend project, controllers should be thin and services should be responsible for validation, orchestration, and persistence coordination. In this RAG knowledge assistant project, document content is saved into MySQL and then split into reusable chunks. These chunks will be used later for embedding generation and vector search.",
  "sourceType": "MANUAL",
  "sourceUri": "manual-input"
}


### list document chunks after update
GET {{host}}/api/documents/1/chunks


### delete document
DELETE {{host}}/api/documents/1


### try to delete space
DELETE {{host}}/api/spaces/1